12.  RELATED DATA SETS  
                                                        
     Several related data sets exist online through NCDS.  
                                                                                
     1) The Climate Research Unit Global Temperature Deviations data set
        contains surface air and marine air temperature anomalies derived
        from the World Weather Records (WWR).  These data are available
        online through NCDS in Common Data Format (CDF).  To access these
        CDFs, specify the following as input within the Data Applications
        subsystem of NCDS.

                      NCDS$DATA:CLIM-RSRCH-U_TMP-DEV

     2) The Angell Global Temperature Deviations data set contains zonal
        temperature deviations derived from radiosonde measurements
        compiled in Monthly Climatic Data for the World, published by the
        National Climatic Data Center.  These data are available online
        through NCDS in Common Data Format (CDF).  To access these CDFs,
        specify the following as input within the Data Applications
        subsystem of NCDS.

                      NCDS$DATA:ANGELL_TMP_DEV

     3) The GISS Temperature Deviations data set contains monthly
        temperature deviations for the period 1880 through 1988 and is
        available online through NCDS in Common Data Format (CDF).  To
        access these CDFs, specify the following as input within the Data
        Applications subsystem of NCDS.
                                                     
                      NCDS$DATA:GISS-TMP-DEV_MON-GLB
                      NCDS$DATA:GISS-TMP-DEV_MON-NH  
                      NCDS$DATA:GISS-TMP-DEV_MON-SH
                      NCDS$DATA:GISS-TMP-DEV_MON-ZONE  
                      NCDS$DATA:GISS-TMP-DEV_MON-BOXES
                      NCDS$DATA:GISS-TMP-DEV_MON-SUBBOXES

                                                                                
